articles/18432-Mark-Moores-Blog-Eastern-outlook.html |last=Moore |first=Mark |accessdate=2008-10-13 |publisher=The Hockey News |title=Eastern Conference Picks |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081012010556/http://www.thehockeynews.com/articles/18432-Mark-Moores-Blog-Eastern-outlook.html |archivedate=12 October 2008 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Some, including ''The Hockey News''' Adam Proteau, placed the team to miss the playoffs altogether.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehockeynews.com/articles/18106-Screen-Shots-200809-Eastern-Conference-predictions.html |last=Proteau |first=Adam |date=September 25, 2008 |accessdate=2008-12-18 |title=Screen Shots: 2008\u201309 Eastern Conference predictions |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081110110149/http://thehockeynews.com/articles/18106-Screen-Shots-200809-Eastern-Conference-predictions.html |archive-date=November 10, 2008 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> However, if they make the playoffs, Proteau plans to\n<blockquote>&ldquo;Commission a musical mash-up consisting of Alanis Morissette and Paul Anka music \u2013 and Tom Green's short-lived professional rap career \u2013 and listen to it on repeat for an entire drive from Toronto to Ottawa. And back, even.&rdquo;</blockquote>'''The Hockey News''', December 11, 2008<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehockeynews.com/articles/21060-Screen-Shots-Ready-to-count-em-out.html |last=Proteau |first=Adam |date=December 11, 2008 |accessdate=2008-12-18 |title=Screen Shots: Ready to count 'em out |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081217144206/http://thehockeynews.com/articles/21060-Screen-Shots-Ready-to-count-em-out.html |archivedate=17 December 2008 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nAfter changing coaches and improving play, the Senators were not able to qualify for the playoffs. On March 31, the Senators were mathematically eliminated from the playoff race.\n\n==Awards and records==\n\n===Records===\n* NHL record for consecutive team games with assists from the start of a season by a defenseman (8) \u2013 [[Filip Kuba]].\n* March 5, 2009 \u2013 [[Jason Spezza]] scored at 0:12 of the first period to set a new Senators record for the fastest goal from the start of a game.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://senators.nhl.com/team/app/?service=page&page=Recap&gameNumber=959&season=20082009&gameType=2 |title=Ottawa Senators Recap: Edmonton @ Ottawa |date=March 6, 2009 |accessdate=2009-03-06 |publisher=Ottawa Senators| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090307145735/http://senators.nhl.com/team/app/?service=page&page=Recap&gameNumber=959&season=20082009&gameType=2| archivedate= 7 March 2009 | url-status= dead}}</ref>\n* April 7, 2009 \u2013 Team won ninth consecutive home game to set new team record.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://senators.nhl.com/team/app/?service=page&page=Recap&gameNumber=1189&season=20082009&gameType=2 |title=Ottawa Senators - Recap: Boston @ Ottawa - 04 July 2009 |date=April 8, 2009 |accessdate=2009-04-08 |publisher=Ottawa Senators |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100109235045/http://senators.nhl.com/team/app/?service=page |archivedate=9 January 2010 }}</ref>\n\n===Milestones===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"52%\"\n| colspan=\"10\" align=\"center\" | '''Regular season'''\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#dddddd\"\n| '''Player''' || '''Milestone''' || '''Reached'''\n|-\n| [[Chris Phillips]] || 700th NHL game || October 4, 2008\n|-\n| [[Filip Kuba]] || First assist with Ottawa<br />First point with Ottawa || October 4, 2008\n|-\n| [[Alex Auld]] || First game with Ottawa<br />First start with Ottawa<br />First win with Ottawa || October 5, 2008\n|-\n| [[Alexandre R. Picard|Alexandre Picard]] || First goal with Ottawa<br />First point with Ottawa || October 11, 2008\n|-\n| [[Chris Kelly (ice hockey)|Chris Kelly]] || 100th career point || October 18, 2008\n|-\n| Alexandre Picard || 100th NHL game|| October 25, 2008\n|-\n| [[Dany Heatley]] || 291st career point with Ottawa<br/>(passing [[Shawn McEachern]] for 7th on<br/>Senators' all-time point scoring list)|| November 6, 2008\n|-\n| [[Jesse Winchester (ice hockey)|Jesse Winchester]] || First NHL goal|| November 6, 2008\n|-\n| [[Zack Smith (ice hockey)|Zack Smith]] || First NHL game || November 29, 2008\n|-\n| [[Brendan Bell (ice hockey)|Brendan Bell]] || First goal with Ottawa<br />First assist with Ottawa<br />First point with Ottawa|| December 3, 2008\n|-\n| [[Jason Spezza]] || Second career Hat-Trick || December 6, 2008\n|-\n| Dany Heatley || 500th career point || December 20, 2008\n|-\n| [[Jason Smith (ice hockey)|Jason Smith]]  || First goal with Ottawa<br />First point with Ottawa || December 20, 2008\n|-\n| [[Martin Gerber]] || 100th game in net for Ottawa<sup>A</sup> || January 8, 2009\n|-\n| Mike Fisher || 500th regular-season NHL game || January 13, 2009\n|-\n| [[Peter Regin]] ||First NHL game || January 20, 2009\n|-\n| Peter Regin ||First NHL goal || January 29, 2009\n|-\n| Daniel Alfredsson || 900th regular-season NHL game || February 1, 2009\n|-\n| [[Shean Donovan]] || 900th regular-season NHL game || February 14, 2009\n|-\n| Jason Spezza || 391st point with Senators<br/>(passing [[Mari\u00e1n Hossa|Marian Hossa]] for fifth on<br/>Senators' all-time point scoring list) || February 14, 2009\n|-\n| Jason Smith || 1,000th regular-season NHL game || February 17, 2009\n|-\n| Daniel Alfredsson || 350th NHL goal || March 7, 2009\n|-\n| Jason Spezza || 400th point with Senators<br/>(passing [[Radek Bonk]] for fourth on<br/>Senators' all-time point scoring list) || March 11, 2009\n|-\n| Brian Elliott || First NHL shutout. || March 29, 2009\n|}\n\n* <sup>A</sup>Later demoted to Binghamton and released on waivers, it was also his last game with Ottawa.\n\n==Transactions==\n* May 29, 2008 - re-signed [[Jesse Winchester (ice hockey)|Jesse Winchester]]\n* June 2, 2008 - signed [[Peter Regin]] to entry-level contract.\n* June 13, 2008 - signed Craig Hartsburg to a three-year contract.\n* June 18, 2008 - re-signed [[Matt Carkner]] to a two-year contract.\n* June 20, 2008 - placed [[Ray Emery]] on waivers. (bought out)\n* June 20, 2008 - re-signed [[Chris Kelly (ice hockey)|Chris Kelly]]\n* July 1, 2008 - signed [[Alex Auld]] to two-year contract\n* July 2, 2008 - re-signed [[Shean Donovan]]\n* July 2, 2008 - signed [[Jarkko Ruutu]]\n* July 7, 2008 - re-signed [[Greg Mauldin]] to a one-year, [[two-way contract]].\n* July 8, 2008 - signed [[Jason Smith (ice hockey)|Jason Smith]]\n* July 11, 2008 - signed [[Mitchell O'Keefe]] to a one-year, entry-level contract.\n* July 11, 2008 - signed [[Brendan Bell (ice hockey)|Brendan Bell]] to a one-year, two-way contract.\n* July 11, 2008 - signed [[Curtis Hunt]] to a three-year contract.\n* July 28, 2008 - re-signed [[Jeff Glass (ice hockey)|Jeff Glass]] to a one-year, two-way contract.\n* July 29, 2008 - re-signed [[Josh Hennessy]] to a two-year, two-way contract.\n* July 31, 2008 - re-signed [[Antoine Vermette]] to a two-year contract.\n* August 11, 2008 - re-signed [[Geoff Waugh]] to a one-year, two-way contract.\n* August 14, 2008 - signed [[Zack Smith (ice hockey)|Zack Smith]] to an entry-level contract.\n* September 4, 2008 - signed [[Brad Isbister]] to a one-year, two-way contract.\n* September 27, 2008 - re-signed [[Luke Richardson]] to a one-year, two-way contract.\n* September 27, 2008 - assigned [[Brad Isbister]] to Binghamton. Isbister declined and was loaned to [[EV Zug]] on October 4.\n* October 30, 2008 - re-signed [[Daniel Alfredsson]] to a four-year contract extension.<ref>{{cite news |work=TSN.ca |url=https://www.tsn.ca/nhl/teams/story/?id=254198&hubname=nhl-senators&lid=sublink01&lpos=headlines_nhl-senators |title=Alfredsson and Senators agree to four-year deal |date=October 30, 2008 |accessdate=2008-10-30}}</ref>\n* November 27, 2008 - placed [[Luke Richardson]] on waivers. (retired)<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.globesports.com/servlet/story/RTGAM.20081127.wsptsens_richardson27/GSStory/GlobeSportsHockey/?page=rss&id=RTGAM.20081127.wsptsens_richardson27 |title=Senators put defenceman Richardson on waivers |work=globesports.com |date=January 22, 2009 |author=Canadian Press| accessdate= 4 February 2009 <!--DASHBot-->}}</ref>\n* January 22, 2009 - placed [[Martin Gerber]] on waivers. (assigned to Binghamton)<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.globesports.com/servlet/story/RTGAM.20090122.wsptgerber22/GSStory/GlobeSportsHockey/?page=rss&id=RTGAM.20090122.wsptgerber22 |title=Senators place Gerber on waivers |work=globesports.com |date=January 22, 2009 |author=Canadian Press| accessdate= 4 February 2009 <!--DASHBot-->}}</ref>\n* February 2, 2009 - fire Craig Hartsburg as head coach, elevate [[Cory Clouston]] to head coach.\n* March 4, 2009 - re-signed [[Filip Kuba]] to three-year contract extension at $3.7 million per season.\n* March 9, 2009 - signed free agent [[Craig Schira]] to three-year entry-level contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://senators.nhl.com/team/app/?service=page&page=NewsPage&articleid=412994 |publisher=Ottawa Senators |title=Bulletin: Senators sign Vancouver Giants defenceman Craig Schira  |accessdate=2009-03-09| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090315031547/http://senators.nhl.com/team/app/?service=page&page=NewsPage&articleid=412994| archivedate= 15 March 2009 | url-status= dead}}</ref>\n\n'''Source:''' senators.nhl.com\n\n===Trades===\n{| border=1 style=\"border-collapse:collapse\" bordercolor=\"#DFDFDF\"  cellpadding=\"5\" \n|- \n| June 20, 2008<br />\n|  valign=\"top\"| To [[Nashville Predators]]<hr>1st-round pick (18th overall) in [[2008 NHL Entry Draft|2008]]<br />3rd-round pick in [[2009 NHL Entry Draft|2009]]\n|  valign=\"top\"| To [[Ottawa Senators]]<hr>1st-round pick (15th overall) in [[2008 NHL Entry Draft|2008]]\n|- bgcolor=\"eeeeee\"\n| June 25, 2008<ref>{{cite news |url=http://senators.nhl.com/team/app?articleid=366961&page=NewsPage&service=page |title=Senators Acquire 2009 5th-round Pick from Phoenix for McGratta