8-08-14| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080817210110/http://senators.nhl.com/team/app/?service=page&page=NewsPage&articleid=379713| archivedate= 17 August 2008 | url-status= dead}}</ref> In previous years, Elmira had accepted players from Binghamton on a player-by-player basis. The new agreement formalized the arrangement of Elmira as the primary affiliate of Binghamton and the secondary affiliate of Ottawa.<ref name=\"elmira-bulletin\"/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[2008\u201309 NHL season]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Ottawa Senators}}\n{{Ottawa Senators seasons}}\n{{2008\u201309 NHL season by team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2008-09 Ottawa Senators Season}}\n[[Category:Ottawa Senators seasons]]\n[[Category:2008\u201309 NHL season by team|Ottawa Senators season, 2008-09]]\n[[Category:2008\u201309 in Canadian ice hockey by team|Ottawa]]\n", "name_user": "LilHelpa", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo: though\u2192through; mos", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2008%E2%80%9309_Ottawa_Senators_season"}
